definitions.definition: Of an electrical cable, having connector pins at one end wired to different pins at the other; for example, pin 1 to pin 2, pin 2 to pin 4 etc.;  contrasted with straight-through .

subdefinitions.definition: Configured so that the transmit signals at one end are connected to the receive signals at the other.
subdefinitions.label_groups: in particular , computing , of an Ethernet cable

main_definition: Of an electrical cable, having connector pins at one end wired to different pins at the other; for example, pin 1 to pin 2, pin 2 to pin 4 etc.;  contrasted with straight-through .
